{{Quote|Lord Gyles.|Sansa Stark greets Gyles Rosby|The Pointy End}}'''Gyles Rosby''' is a recurring background character in the [[Season 1|first season]]. He was played by an unidentified extra and debuts in &quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]].&quot; He is the Lord of [[Rosby]] and the head of [[House Rosby]], a noble house of the [[Crownlands]], who is constantly present at the royal court in the [[Red Keep]].

sections.Biography:
===[[Season 1]]===
Lord Gyles attends the Tourney of the Hand and is seated next to Septa [[Mordane]] for the first day of the jousts.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Lord Gyles is present at the session in which [[Janos Slynt]] is created [[House Slynt|Lord Slynt]] and given the castle of [[Harrenhal]] and later [[Knight|Ser]] [[Barristan Selmy]] is dismissed from the [[Kingsguard]]. When [[Sansa Stark]] appears to ask for mercy for her [[Eddard Stark|father]], Lord Gyles is greeted by the young lady, though he doesn't answer.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Lord Gyles is also present at court when the troubadour [[Marillion]] is forced to perform a limerick in which he ridiculed the late King [[Robert Baratheon|Robert]] and Queen [[Cersei Lannister|Cersei]]. Alongside the rest of the courtiers, Lord Gyles claps after King [[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey]] begins to clap sarcastically.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Fire and Blood]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
